  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Asia Region: Protecting Migrant Workers in COVID-19 Socio-Economic Recovery by Engaging with Public and Private Sectors to Strengthen Ethical Recruitment and Employment Practices</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Migrant workers from the Philippines and Viet Nam are among the largest groups in Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR), China. Despite limited availability of recent studies and research on migrant workers in Macao SAR, China, there are reports of certain risks for migrant workers in recruitment and employment practices including being subject to high recruitment fees and receiving lower wages than local workers. Furthermore, border closures and travel restrictions during the COVID-19 pandemic have adversely impacted the tourism-dependent economy, triggering job losses of migrant workers. The overall objective of the proposed project is to contribute to the protection of migrant workers from the Philippines and Viet Nam in COVID-19 socio-economic recovery by strengthening the implementation of ethical recruitment and employment practices. This will be achieved through engaging labour authorities in countries of origin and destination to strengthen services and response to migrant workers&apos; needs at varying stages of their migration journey; working with private sector labour actors and employers to promote compliance with national regulation and commit to meet international ethical recruitment standards; and improving information access for migrant workers to better inform their migration-related decisions and strengthening support from the civil society, migrant worker led organizations and Migrant Resource Centres.</narrative>
  </description>
